
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-padma-ideas-problem-statement-03.txt'>
    <title>"Problem Statement for Identity Enabled Networks", Padma Pillay-Esnault, Mohamed Boucadair, Giuseppe Fioccola, Christian Jacquenet, Axel Nennker</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-padma-ideas-problem-statement-03.txt</link>
    <description>This problem statement examines how existing protocols that separate identifiers from their location may benefit from the concept of identity.  The proposal laid out herein advocates for a standardized identity/identifier network infrastructure that provides a framework to support identity services in addition to enhancing existing identifier/location mapping and resolution services.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-07-03T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
